Description: Wavy handled jar of marl clay with offset neck, everted rim, two applied wavy handles. Body deformed on one side.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: E. R. Ayrton & W. L. S. Loat, 'Pre-dynastic cemetery at El Mahasna' (London, 1911), p. 21 pl. xxxiii. 19. Pot visible in situ in pl. ix.44. Type like Wavy handled W24 in Petrie’s Corpus of Prehistoric pottery.
